Errol Velile Present, the former Luthuli House employee alleged to have also been a cash in transit robber was granted bail on Monday morning. According to News24,Presen, and his co-accused  Itumeleng Manama, 40, Bheki Biyela, 38, and Zakhele Zondi, 37, were all granted bail at the Roodepoort Magistrates Court. The four men were arrested and charged with robbery with aggravating circumstances for being part of an alleged heist in Dobsonville, Soweto, on July 4. In granting bail, Magistrate John Baloyi said the State did not provide tangible evidence and that witnesses who took part in an identity parade could not place any of the men at the scene of the crime. There was no CCTV footage available and the accused's fingerprints were not found on the getaway cars and a DNA blood sample found at the scene could not be linked to the any of the accused, he said. In addition, Baloyi said the men were not found in possession of any money and firearms. "The State's case can be described as weak and non-existent," Baloyi said and granted the men R4 000 bail each.